               <head>Johannes Climacus</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <author key="person_268286342">St. John Scholasticus, called Climacus</author>
                     <title>Scala spiritualis and Sermo ad pastorem</title>
                     <note>Revision made c. 1418 by <persName key="person_29617842" role="trl">Ambrogio Traversari</persName> of an earlier translation into Latin. The contents are in the same order as in the first edition, Toledo, 1505.</note>
                     <msItem n="a">
                        <locus from="1r">(fol. 1r)</locus>
                        <title type="desc">Traversari’s dedicatory letter to Fra Matteo Guidoni, prior of S. Maria degli Angeli, Florence (d. 1421)</title>
                        <incipit>Domino amantissimo et merito venerabili patri Matheo Ambrosius. Hortatus es domine amantissime</incipit>
                        <note>Pr. <title>Amb. Trau. Epist.</title> ed. P. Canneto, Florence, 1759, Lib. xxiii, 7, col. 962–4.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="b">
                        <locus from="1v">(fol. 1v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Vita sancti Iohannis Scolastici sub compendio a Daniele monacho scripta</rubric>
                        <incipit>Quenam hunc divinum virum civitas tulerit</incipit>
                        <note>
                           <title>B.H.L.</title> 4381.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="c">
                        <locus from="3v">(fol. 3v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Epistola Iohannis abbatis Raithunensis ad Iohannem abbatem montis Synay Scolasticum cognominatum</rubric>
                        <incipit>Domino singulariter mirabili equali angelis</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="d">
                        <locus from="4r">(fol. 4r)</locus>
                        <rubric>Prefacio Iohannis Scolastiri in librum qui Climax dicitur. Responsio: Iohannes Iohanni salutem</rubric>
                        <incipit>Accepi convenientissimam honestissimo tuo atque impassibili instituto</incipit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="e">
                        <locus from="4v">(fol. 4v)</locus>
                        <title key="work_2469">Scala Spiritualis</title>
                        <rubric>Incipit sermo primus De inanis vite abrenunciacione</rubric>
                        <incipit>Cum summe <sic>incomphensibilis</sic> atque incircumscripte bonitatis deus noster</incipit>
                        <explicit>
                           <locus from="68r" to="68r">(fol. 68r)</locus> et erit in infinita secula Amen.</explicit>
                        <finalRubric>Explicit Gradus trigesimus et ultimus <sic>spiritalis</sic> scale a Iohanne Scolastico edite feliciter;</finalRubric>
                        <msItem>
                           <locus from="68r">(fol. 68r)</locus>
                           <rubric>Eiusdem sermo ad pastorem incipit in quo docetur qualis esse debeat racionalium ovium pastor</rubric>
                           <incipit>In inferiori quidem libro extremum</incipit>
                           <explicit>
                              <locus from="71v" to="71v">(fol. 71v)</locus> et perfeccione sua beata est.</explicit>
                           <finalRubric>Finit sermo ad pastorem Deo gracias</finalRubric>
                        </msItem>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="g">
                        <locus from="71v">(fol. 71v)</locus>
                        <rubric>Commendacio eiusdem Iohannis Scolastici librique a se editi a Iohanne abbate Raithensis monasterii, ubi liber fere totus brevissime ac mistice exponitur laudaturque scribens in hunc modum ut sequitur</rubric>
                        <incipit>Qualem me esse oportere scripsisti</incipit>
                        <explicit>
                           <locus from="72v" to="72v">(fol. 72v)</locus> Caritas autem Deus est Amen.</explicit>
                        <finalRubric>Explicit feliciter Deo gratias qui dedit incipere et finire. Sub anno domini <hi rend="smallcaps">mcccclv</hi> die lune in festo Sancti Mauritii xxi die mensis Septembris, Venedis, in Murano, in monasterio sancti Cipriani ordinis Sancti Benedicti per fratrem Iacobum de Polonia ordinis predicti Crac<supplied>oviensis</supplied> diocesis</finalRubric>
                        <note>(PL XXVc)</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
